snippet.textDisplay:
Do you young guys know there is a very dark side to early SX? (Of course you did not) Yes, it even included murder. This is the "Dave Despain show", (good show), interviewing Jeff Emig in 2015. But at the end, (min 20:05), Dave describes the dark history of SX's beginnings. Back when this crime was concluded, I actually found the victims sisters phone number on line, and called her to congratulate their family for the closure. This is the man who started SX in 1972. (start at min 20:05, but the Emig story is cool)

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=In7jQ_LT4sk

snippet.textDisplay: Ken Roczen pulled off a great pass on Ozzy for the lead.  Roczen was able to clear the step off jump, (instead of stepping off of it), and clear the next 2 triples into the corner, (that is where Ken won this race).  He was then in position to take Ozzy's line and keep Ozzy from jumping a big double that followed.  It was a beautiful move, with a little contact, perfect.  Roczen then goes on to win by over 8 seconds. What does Ken say on the podium?  "Sorry to Zack".   Maybe this is why Ken will not win this championship.
